---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'

// Set prerender to true to ensure this page is statically generated during build
export const prerender = true
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy | Gradiant">
  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-3xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert">
      <p class="text-sm italic mb-4">Last updated: March 15, 2025</p>

      <p>
        At Gradiant, we take your privacy seriously. This Privacy Policy
        explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information
        when you use our service.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">
        1. Information We Collect
      </h2>
      <p>We collect information that you provide directly to us when you:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4">
        <li>Create an account</li>
        <li>Fill out forms</li>
        <li>Participate in therapy sessions</li>
        <li>Contact customer support</li>
        <li>Respond to surveys</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This information may include your name, email address, professional
        credentials, and content generated during therapy sessions.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">
        2. Security and Encryption
      </h2>
      <p>
        We utilize advanced security technologies, including Fully Homomorphic
        Encryption (FHE), to protect your data. Our platform is designed with
        HIPAA compliance in mind, featuring:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4">
        <li>End-to-end encryption</li>
        <li>Key partitioning for enhanced security</li>
        <li>Secure key management with rotation periods</li>
        <li>Session-based encryption with key scoping</li>
        <li>Homomorphic operations for secure analytics</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We maintain appropriate administrative, technical, and physical
        safeguards to protect Personal Information against accidental or
        unlawful destruction, accidental loss, unauthorized alteration,
        unauthorized disclosure or access, misuse, and any other unlawful form
        of processing.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">3. Data Usage</h2>
      <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4">
        <li>Provide, maintain, and improve our services</li>
        <li>Process and complete transactions</li>
        <li>Send transactional messages</li>
        <li>Generate anonymized analytics and insights</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        All analytics are performed on encrypted data using homomorphic
        operations, ensuring your privacy while gaining valuable therapeutic
        insights.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">4. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell or rent personal information to third parties. We may
        share information in the following circumstances:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4">
        <li>With your consent</li>
        <li>
          With service providers who need access to perform services for us
        </li>
        <li>To comply with laws or to protect rights and safety</li>
        <li>
          In connection with a business transfer (merger, acquisition, etc.)
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">5. HIPAA Compliance</h2>
      <p>
        As a service provider to healthcare professionals, we maintain HIPAA
        compliance and implement all required safeguards for Protected Health
        Information (PHI), including:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4">
        <li>Business Associate Agreements with covered entities</li>
        <li>Regular security assessments</li>
        <li>Comprehensive audit logging</li>
        <li>Employee training on privacy and security</li>
        <li>Breach notification procedures</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">6. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding your personal
        information, including:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4">
        <li>Access to your personal information</li>
        <li>Correction of inaccurate information</li>
        <li>Deletion of your information</li>
        <li>Restriction of processing</li>
        <li>Data portability</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise these rights, please contact us using the information below.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">
        7. Changes to This Policy
      </h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you
        of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and
        updating the "Last Updated" date.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">8. Contact Information</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us
        at:
      </p>
      <p>
        Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@gradiant.com">privacy@gradiant.com</a><br
        />
        Phone: +1-800-123-4567
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
